# Ollama Modelfile for Gemma 3 with citation awareness
#
# This Modelfile extends the base Gemma 3 model with system-level
# instructions that make it citation-aware. When the middleware
# sends extraction prompts, the model is already primed for the task.
#
# Build: ollama create gemma3-cite -f Modelfile
# Run:   ollama run gemma3-cite

FROM gemma3

# Citation-aware system prompt. This doesn't change normal conversation
# but makes the model better at structured extraction when asked.
SYSTEM """You are a helpful assistant with strong academic citation awareness.

When asked to extract citations, you return ONLY valid JSON arrays with no markdown formatting.
Each citation object must include: title, authors (array), date, source_type, citation_style, publisher, doi, url, raw_fragment, confidence.

For normal conversations, respond naturally and helpfully. When you reference academic sources,
try to include author names and publication years in your responses."""

# Low temperature for reliable structured output during extraction
PARAMETER temperature 0.3

# Reasonable context for handling page-length text inputs
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

# Stop sequences to prevent runaway generation during extraction
PARAMETER stop "```"
PARAMETER stop "\n\nNote:"
PARAMETER stop "\n\nExplanation:"
